    {
      "content": "What is Azure Site Recovery?",
      "pos": [
        1435,
        1463
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Azure Site Recovery contributes to your business continuity and disaster recovery (BCDR) strategy by orchestrating replication, failover and recovery of virtual machines and physical servers.",
      "pos": [
        1465,
        1660
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Machines can be replicated to Azure, or to a secondary on-premises data center.",
      "pos": [
        1661,
        1740
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Read more about <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Site Recovery<ept id=\"p1\">](site-recovery-overview.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        1741,
        1806
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How does it protect on-premises resources?",
      "pos": [
        1811,
        1853
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Site Recovery helps protect your on-premises resources by orchestrating, simplifying replication, failover and failback in a number of <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>deployment scenarios<ept id=\"p1\">](site-recovery-overview.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        1855,
        2040
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you want to protect your on-premises VMware virtual machines or Windows or Linux physical servers here's how Site Recovery can help:",
      "pos": [
        2041,
        2176
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Allows VMware users to replicate virtual machines to Azure.",
      "pos": [
        2180,
        2239
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Allows the replication of physical on-premises servers to Azure.",
      "pos": [
        2242,
        2306
      ]
