      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Component servers<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—The process server, configuration server, and master target server"
    },
    {
      "content": "Considerations for the source environment",
      "pos": [
        7661,
        7702
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Maximum disk size<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—The current maximum size of the disk that can be attached to a virtual machine is 1 TB.",
      "pos": [
        7706,
        7815
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Thus the maximum size of a source disk that can be replicated is also limited to 1 TB.",
      "pos": [
        7816,
        7902
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7905,
        8067
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Maximum size per source<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—The maximum size of a single source machine is 31 TB (with 31 disks) and with a D14 instance provisioned for the master target server."
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Number of sources per master target server<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—Multiple source machines can be protected with a single master target server.",
      "pos": [
        8071,
        8195
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, a single source machine can’t be protected across multiple master target servers, because as disks replicate, a VHD that mirrors the size of the disk is created on Azure blob storage and attached as a data disk to the master target server.",
      "pos": [
        8196,
        8444
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Maximum daily change rate per source<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—There are three factors that need to be considered when considering the recommended change rate per source.",
      "pos": [
        8449,
        8597
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For the target based considerations two IOPS are required on the target disk for each operation on the source.",
      "pos": [
        8598,
        8708
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is because a read of old data and a write of the new data will happen on the target disk.",
      "pos": [
        8709,
        8803
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Daily change rate supported by the process server<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—A source machine can't span multiple process servers.",
      "pos": [
        8811,
        8918
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A single process server can support up to 1 TB of daily change rate.",
      "pos": [
        8919,
        8987
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Hence 1 TB is the maximum daily data change rate supported for a source machine.",
      "pos": [
        8988,
        9068
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Maximum throughput supported by the target disk<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—Maximum churn per source disk can't be more than 144 GB/day (with 8K write size).",
      "pos": [
        9076,
        9209
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See the table in the master target section for the throughput and IOPs of the target for various write sizes.",
      "pos": [
        9210,
        9319
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This number must be divided by two because each source IOP generates 2 IOPS on the target disk.",
      "pos": [
        9320,
        9415
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Refer <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Scalability and Performance Targets when using Premium Storage<ept id=\"p1\">](../storage/storage-scalability-targets.md#scalability-targets-for-premium-storage-accounts)</ept> while configuring target for Premium Storage account.",
      "pos": [
        9416,
        9632
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Maximum throughput supported by the storage account<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—A source can't span multiple storage accounts.",
      "pos": [
        9639,
        9741
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Given that a storage account takes a maximum of 20,000 requests per second and that each source IOP generates 2 IOPS at the master target server, we recommend you keep the number of IOPS across the source to 10,000.",
