    {
      "content": "These credentials are only used for push installation of the Mobility service and you'll provide them when you add a machine to a protection group.",
      "pos": [
        53512,
        53659
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the provided account isn't a domain account you'll need to disable Remote User Access control on the local machine.",
      "pos": [
        53663,
        53781
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To do this add the LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy DWORD registry entry with a value of 1 under HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System.",
      "pos": [
        53782,
        53953
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To add the registry entry from a CLI open cmd or powershell and enter <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">`REG ADD HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System /v LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy /t REG_DWORD /d 1`</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        53954,
        54166
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Automatically push install the mobility service on Linux servers:",
      "pos": [
        54171,
        54236
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        54243,
        54426
      ],
      "content": "Install the latest updates for the process server as described in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step 5: Install latest updates<ept id=\"p1\">](#step-5-install-latest-updates)</ept>, and make sure that the process server is available."
